fields.bio: Just trying to enjoy a donut and some TV.
Eat my shorts! Always causing trouble, but with a heart of gold.
The smartest one in the family.

fields.title: Skateboarding Adventures
fields.content: I just pulled off an insane trick at the Springfield skatepark! It was totally awesome! Can't wait to do it again, dude.

fields.title: Prank of the Day
fields.content: I put a bucket of water above the door to Principal Skinner's office. The look on his face was priceless when it fell! Classic.

fields.title: A Donut a Day Keeps the Stress Away
fields.content: Another day, another donut. I swear, they make everything better. And a beer at Moe's never hurts either. Cheers to the good life!

fields.title: Lunar Loco
fields.content: I tried to build a rocket out of junk and sent it to space. Failed miserably, but at least it was a blast!
That sounds awesome, Bart! Just be careful!
I told you skateboarding was dangerous! Always thinking you’re invincible.
I got this, mom! I’m the king of tricks!
I can't believe you did that to Skinner. You’re a real troublemaker, Bart!
It was hilarious, Lisa! You should have seen his face!
That rocket thing was wild, Bart. Good try though! I’m just glad you didn’t blow up the whole house.
You’re nuts, Bart! But I gotta admit, it was fun to watch. I mean, who else would try to launch a rocket made of junk?
What were you thinking, Bart? You should've at least had a proper plan! You could’ve used all that junk for something useful, like building a treehouse for me.
I agree with Lisa. You should’ve been more careful, Bart. But, knowing you, I can’t say I’m surprised. You never really think things through, do you?
Hey, I had a vision! It wasn’t a total failure – we learned something, right? I just need a bigger rocket next time... maybe a bigger house too, just in case.
Next time, how about we stick to something less explosive? Like a cool skateboard trick? At least I won't have to worry about my hair catching fire.
You know, maybe we can turn this into a family project. Build a rocket, go to space... at least it would be a nice family outing. Just make sure it’s not made of junk next time.

Bart, you just can't help yourself, can you? I mean, sure, I admire your creativity... but you really need to start thinking things through. A rocket made of junk? Seriously?

Imagine if you'd just used that energy for something more productive. We could’ve built something useful. Instead, we have a burnt-out lawn and a few singed hairs. Let’s leave the space exploration to NASA, okay?
